---
import LegalLayout from "@/components/layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
import LegalContact from "@/components/legal/LegalContact.astro";
import { LEGAL_LAST_UPDATED } from "@/data/content";
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How AUXO Data Labs collects, uses, and protects personal data from website visitors, inquiry contacts, and users who choose analytics or scheduling tools."
  lastUpdated={LEGAL_LAST_UPDATED}
>
  <div class="legal-callout">
    <p>
      <strong>Scope.</strong> This notice covers <strong>auxodata.com</strong>,
      contact requests, cookie choices, and optional meeting scheduling. It
      does <strong>not</strong> govern client datasets processed under separate
      services agreements.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>1. Controller and Scope</h2>
  <p>
    AUXO Data Labs is the trading name of <strong>Rapple International FZE</strong>,
    based in Dubai, United Arab Emirates. For the personal data described in
    this notice, Rapple International FZE acts as the controller.
  </p>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy applies to information collected through our public
    website, direct email contact, the website contact form, and the optional
    scheduling tools linked from the site.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
  <h3>2.1 Information You Provide Directly</h3>
  <p>
    If you contact us or request a meeting, we may collect the information you
    choose to submit, including:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Identity and contact details:</strong> name, work email address, and company.</li>
    <li><strong>Inquiry details:</strong> subject line, message content, and any business context you include.</li>
    <li><strong>Scheduling details:</strong> meeting preferences or calendar information if you choose to book time with us.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>2.2 Information Collected Automatically</h3>
  <p>
    When you browse the site, we may collect technical and usage data such as
    IP address, browser type, device characteristics, pages viewed, referring
    URLs, approximate interaction timestamps, and aggregated engagement events.
  </p>
  <p>
    Analytics storage remains disabled until you opt in through our cookie
    controls.
  </p>

  <h3>2.3 Information Stored on Your Device</h3>
  <p>
    The site also stores limited browser-side data to support core UX:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Consent preferences:</strong> your cookie-based consent choices.</li>
    <li><strong>Theme preference:</strong> your selected light or dark theme.</li>
    <li><strong>Temporary form draft:</strong> an unfinished contact-form draft, stored locally for up to 24 hours if you start typing.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. How We Use Personal Data</h2>
  <table class="legal-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Examples</th>
        <th>Primary Legal Basis</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Operate and secure the site</td>
        <td>Core page delivery, stability, abuse prevention, diagnostics</td>
        <td>Legitimate interests</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Respond to enquiries</td>
        <td>Replying to emails and contact-form submissions</td>
        <td>Legitimate interests or pre-contract steps</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Arrange meetings you request</td>
        <td>Opening and handling calendar-booking flows</td>
        <td>Legitimate interests or pre-contract steps</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Remember preferences</td>
        <td>Consent status, theme selection, form-draft restore</td>
        <td>Legitimate interests and user-requested functionality</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Measure site usage</td>
        <td>Google Analytics reporting and engagement events</td>
        <td>Consent</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Meet legal obligations and protect rights</td>
        <td>Recordkeeping, dispute handling, compliance requests</td>
        <td>Legal obligation or legitimate interests</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>4. Cookies, Consent, and Similar Technologies</h2>
  <p>
    We use first-party cookies, local storage, and consent-aware tags to run
    the site and, if you choose, to understand how the site is used.
  </p>
  <p>
    You can accept, reject, or adjust non-essential categories through the
    consent banner or the <strong>Cookie Settings</strong> control in the
    footer. More detail appears in our
    <a href="/legal/cookie-policy">Cookie Policy</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>5. When We Share Data</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell personal data. We share it only when needed to operate the
    site or respond to your request, including with:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Form delivery providers:</strong> for website enquiry routing, including EmailJS.</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics and tag providers:</strong> Google Tag Manager and Google Analytics, but only where the relevant consent basis applies.</li>
    <li><strong>Scheduling providers:</strong> Google Calendar booking flows if you choose to use them.</li>
    <li><strong>Infrastructure and security providers:</strong> vendors that support hosting, delivery, uptime, and abuse prevention.</li>
    <li><strong>Authorities or advisers:</strong> where required by law or reasonably necessary to establish, exercise, or defend legal claims.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. International Transfers</h2>
  <p>
    AUXO operates internationally and some service providers may process data
    outside your country. Where applicable, we rely on appropriate contractual,
    legal, or organisational safeguards for those transfers.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Retention</h2>
  <p>
    We keep personal data only for as long as reasonably necessary for the
    purpose for which it was collected.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Contact enquiries and correspondence:</strong> typically up to 24 months after the last meaningful interaction.</li>
    <li><strong>Consent and preference storage:</strong> until you clear browser storage, change your settings, or the relevant item expires.</li>
    <li><strong>Contact-form draft storage:</strong> up to 24 hours on your device.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal or compliance records:</strong> longer where required for legitimate legal, accounting, or regulatory reasons.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>8. Your Rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on the laws that apply to you, you may have rights to access,
    correct, delete, restrict, or object to certain processing, to receive a
    copy of your data, to withdraw consent for optional analytics, and to lodge
    a complaint with a competent supervisory authority.
  </p>
  <p>
    California residents may also have rights relating to disclosure,
    correction, deletion, and non-discrimination. We do not state that we sell
    personal information, and we do not knowingly activate advertising cookies
    on this site at the time of this update.
  </p>
  <p>
    To exercise a request, email
    <a href="mailto:privacy@auxodata.com">privacy@auxodata.com</a>. We may ask
    for reasonable information to verify identity before acting on the request.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    This site is intended for a professional audience and is not directed to
    children. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children through
    the site.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this notice when the site, our tools, or the law changes. The
    updated version will be posted here with a revised last-updated date.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy questions or rights requests, contact Rapple International FZE
    trading as AUXO Data Labs at
    <a href="mailto:privacy@auxodata.com">privacy@auxodata.com</a>.
  </p>

  <LegalContact
    title="Privacy Contact"
    intro="Use this contact route for privacy questions, correction requests, or concerns about how website data is handled."
    email="privacy@auxodata.com"
  />
</LegalLayout>
